### 1. Lado recebedor — emitir cobrança NFC
### A maquininha solicita um payload assinado pra emitir via NFC à máquina do pagador.
POST http://localhost:8081/v1/nfc/charges
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "terminalId": "T-001",
  "amountCents": 1500,
  "displayLabel": "Padaria São José · #4210",
  "validitySeconds": 120
}

> {%
client.global.set("payload_wire", response.body.payloadWire);
client.global.set("charge_id", response.body.chargeId);
%}

### 2. Lado pagador — apenas validar (mostra ao usuário antes de cobrar)
POST http://localhost:8081/v1/nfc/payments/validate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "payloadWire": "{{payload_wire}}"
}

### 3. Lado pagador — autorizar e disparar Pix via SPI
POST http://localhost:8081/v1/nfc/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "payloadWire": "{{payload_wire}}",
  "payerAccount": {
    "ispb": "99988877",
    "branch": "0001",
    "number": "0000556677",
    "type": "CACC"
  },
  "payerDeviceId": "device-iphone-15"
}

### Health
GET http://localhost:8081/actuator/health

### Prometheus metrics
GET http://localhost:8081/actuator/prometheus
